Rating: 4
I loved this. First dinner I made in a long while that I just swooned over. I expected the "coulis" to be like tomatillo salsa, but it wasn't. It was more concentrated and richer. Was delicious over the salmon and the garlicky rice I served with it. Don't know how anyone could say the sauce has no flavor, since it's full of roasted tomatillos, poblanos and garlic, plus fresh lime and cilantro. Yum!

