Rating: 4
The tomatillo-chile pepper sauce is sensational. I now prepare it in a double batch and use it with many other entrees (pork loin, plain old chicken breasts, etc). I process all but 1/2 poblano until I see how hot it's running, add that at the end if needed. The sauce keeps well for at least a week in fridge and can be warmed gently in the microwave. It also makes a great dip with corn chips. I skin the salmon fillets, skip the peppercorns, serve with sauce under and julienned basil sprinkled over. Last night I used some of my stash to go with Epicurious #102662, spiced pork tenderloin. Great improvement!

